om/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/responsive-web-design.png" alt="" width="550" height="260" /></a></p><p>We&#8217;ve mentioned responsive web design in a few of our blog entries in the past, and with 2013 being the <a href="http://mashable.com/2012/12/11/responsive-web-design/" target="_blank">year of responsive web design</a>, we&#8217;d like to take a closer look into the concept and what&#8217;s behind it.</p><p> <a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/responsive-web-design/#more-3753" class="more-link">Read the rest of this entry &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div class="post" id="post-3384"><h2><a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/implementing-e-commerce-moving-amt-forward/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Implementing E-Commerce: Moving AMT Forward">Implementing E-Commerce: Moving AMT Forward</a></h2><div class="entry"><p align="center"> <a href="/blog/implementing-e-commerce-moving-amt-forward/"><img src="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/title.jpg" alt="Implementing E-Commerce: Moving AMT Forward" title="Implementing E-Commerce: Moving AMT Forward" width="550" height="122" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2820" /></a></p><p>Adding a webshop to your site can be a headache, especially if you have a large sales catalog which has to be migrated online.  You don&#8217;t want your existing site to experience any downtime, and you want customers to find shopping online with you easy and intuitive, while still providing them with the products and information they expect.  When Advanced Marine Technologies wanted to consolidate their product catalogs and add a new online store, they came to Gossamer Threads to give them all the functionality they wanted without any hassle or unnecessary change to their workflow.  Here&#8217;s how we helped AMT make the move into e-commerce smoothly and securely, using Gossamer Links and a custom shopping cart, and implementing a careful and detailed import of AMT&#8217;s multiple product catalogs.</p><p> <a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/implementing-e-commerce-moving-amt-forward/#more-3384" class="more-link">Read the rest of this entry &raquo;</a></p></div></div><div class="navigation"><div class="alignleft"><a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/page/2/" >Older Entries</a></div><div class="alignright"></div></div></div><div id="sidebar"><ul><li><h2>Subscribe</h2><form style="padding: 0 0 30px 0;" action="http://www.feedburner.com/fb/a/emailverify" method="post" target="popupwindow" onsubmit="window.open('http://www.feedburner.com/fb/a/emailverifySubmit?feedId=1528629', 'popupwindow', 'scrollbars=yes,width=550,height=520');return true"><p>Receive an e-mail whenever the blog is updated!</p><p><input id="e-mail-widget-input" type="text" name="email" value="Your e-mail address" /><input type="hidden" value="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~e?ffid=1528629" name="url"/><input type="hidden" value="Gossamer Blog" name="title"/><input type="hidden" name="loc" value="en_US"/><input class="button" type="submit" value="Subscribe" /></p></form></li><li id="text-273931291" class="widget widget_text"><h2 class="widgettitle">About the Blog</h2><div class="textwidget"><p>A place for anything and everything related to Gossamer Threads and its employees, this blog is our way of reaching out and bridging some of the distance between our clients and us.</p></div></li><li id="categories-172602521" class="widget widget_categories"><h2 class="widgettitle">Categories</h2><ul><li class="cat-item cat-item-151"><a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/category/best-practices/" title="View all posts filed under Best Practices">Best Practices</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-6"><a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/category/company-life/" title="Information on company outings, events, and news items.">Company Life</a></li><li class="cat-item cat-item-169"><a href="http://www.gossamer-threads.com/blog/category/consultations/" title="Vi